unty .pay for letter heads\nand envelopes?\nPolities Is Only Blight\nFinancial institutions throughout the\nMiddle West and the Southwest de\nclare that the business outlook could\nhardly be better, yet trade halts.\nCrops, with the exception of corn in\nsome sections, have been unusually\ngood and prices are high. The\ncountry merchants find the conditions\nto be favorable and the banks have a\nplethora of cash in their vaults. The\nfinancial men arc at a loss to find the\nreason for any hesitation. They\nshould not have iar to look. Politics is\nthe only blight on the financial horizon.\nWith elections every two years for con\ngress and tor state offices the whole\nUnited States is kept in a continual\nturmoil. No sooner have the polls\nclosed on one election than a new\ncampaign is launched. If the voters\nwould only do their duty and turn\nout and vote at all elections they\ncould place honest and patriotic men\nin office. Then they could make\ntheir terms of office six or eight years.\nThis would igive farmers, banker,\nmerchants and professional men an\nopportity to attend to business. The\nblight of politics is the sole Uoublei\nThe country, is all right. The\nWoman's National Weekly.\nMarriage Licenses\nI Huston I.. Huff, Fortuna\n.Minnie M. Roberts,\n4 Thad Appleton,\nI Bonnie Campbell,\nj William Roe,\nI May Ritchie,\nI Fred E. Reynolds,\nj Flossie B. Chism,\nFortuna\nProctor\nProctor\nVersailles\nVersailles\nTodd\nTodd\nGreat Package'\nPost Carte\nFREE\nSend only 25 cents to pay for that\ngreat farm publication, the Missouri\nand Kansas Farmer, to be mailed to\nyour address ONE YEAR and you\nyou will receive a great .package of\nFIFTY- TWO post cards FREE,\npostage all paid. .These care are\nmost beautiful creations of art, latest\ndesigns, consisting of Floral, Birth-,\nday Greetings, Thanksgiving,\nChristmas, New Year, Valentine,\nSt. Patrick and Easter. Nothing like\nthis great offer made before. The\nMissouri and Konsas Farmer is one\nof the best farm